# Contributing Guidelines

Thank you for your interest in contributing to our project! We welcome all contributions, including bug fixes and new features.

## Getting Started

1. Fork the repository and clone it to your local machine.
2. Create a new branch for your changes: `git checkout -b my-new-branch`.
3. Make your changes and test them thoroughly.
4. Commit your changes with a descriptive commit message: `git commit -m "Add new feature"`.
5. Push your changes to your fork: `git push origin my-new-branch`.
6. Submit a pull request to the `main` branch of the original repository.

## Code Style

There is no specific code style for this project. However, I would like to refactor the code later to follow the [Google Shell Style Guide](https://google.github.io/styleguide/shellguide.html).

## Issue Tracker

If you encounter any bugs or issues while working on the project, please submit an issue on our [GitHub issue tracker](https://github.com/adia-dev/gitignore/issues) with a detailed description of the problem.

## Code of Conduct

Please note that our project has a [Code of Conduct](https://github.com/adia-dev/gitignore/blob/main/CODE_OF_CONDUCT). We expect all contributors to adhere to its guidelines.

## License

By contributing to our project, you agree that your contributions will be licensed under the [MIT License](https://github.com/adia-dev/gitignore/blob/main/LICENSE).
